The paper discusses the potential of AI to transform project management, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) category. The paper specifically focuses on agile project management, which involves a high degree of collaboration and communication, making it relevant to the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) category. The use of AI for automation and decision-making also falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) category. The paper also discusses the potential for AI to improve project estimation and risk prediction, which relates to the software development (cs.SD) category. Finally, the paper discusses the potential impact of AI on project success rates, which could be relevant to the cybernetics (cs.CY) category.
